text.section:
An individual, at his election, may deduct from his adjusted gross income a standard deduction of:
Six hundred and fifty dollars ($650) for taxable years beginning before December 31, 1996;
Nine hundred dollars ($900) for taxable years beginning after December 31, 1996, but before December 31, 1997;
One thousand two hundred dollars ($1,200) for taxable years beginning after December 31, 1997, but before December 31, 1998;
One thousand five hundred dollars ($1,500) for taxable years beginning after December 31, 1998, but before December 31, 1999;
One thousand seven hundred dollars ($1,700) for taxable years beginning after December 31, 1999, but before December 31, 2000; and
The amount calculated under subsection (2) of this section for taxable years beginning after December 31, 2000.
